===Etymology===
{{etyl|fro}} {{term|azur|lang=fro}}, derived from {{etyl|ar}} {{term|لازورد|لازوَرْد|tr=lāzaward|sc=Arab|lapis lazuli}}, dropping the '''''l''''' as if it were equivalent to the French article {{term|l'|lang=fr}}. The {{etyl|ar}} is from {{etyl|fa}} {{term|لاجورد|tr=lajward|sc=fa-Arab||azure}}, from the region of Lajward in [[w:Turkestan|Turkestan]].

Compare with Italian {{term|azzurro|lang=it}} and Spanish {{term|azul|lang=es}}.

